<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE - Installation
        - Rear Main Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26513.3.3" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Rear Main Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not separate wear sleeve from oil seal; this will damage the seal and
                    engine.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>When replacing the rear main oil seal, note that production engines will not have a wear sleeve.
                    Wear sleeves are only available as a service item included with the replacement rear main oil seal.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651331" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0725.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rear/Wear Sleeve Installer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bolt Rear/Wear Sleeve Installer on end of crankshaft. Make sure crankshaft alignment dowel
                fits in dowel recess hole in the rear/wear sleeve installer.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651332" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0727.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Orientation or rear main oil seal and wear sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dust seal lip</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft side (forward)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve (internal bevel)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position seal and slide onto Rear/Wear Sleeve Installer.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before assembly, lubricate the outer diameter of rubber seal with a solution of dish washing soap
                    and water (approximately 50/50 mix). Do not use other lubricants.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651333" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0748.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Sealant application to secondary crankshaft flange</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before installing wear sleeve and rear main seal oil, apply a 360&#176; bead of Loctite&#174;
                Hydraulic Sealant onto the rear edge of the secondary crankshaft flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651334" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0726.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rear/Wear Sleeve Installer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear/wear sleeve installer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position rear main oil seal and wear sleeve onto the rear/wear sleeve installer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651335" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0724.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve combination on crankshaft</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear/wear sleeve installer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thrust bearing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place thrust bearing and drive nut on threaded shaft. Tighten nut until rear main oil seal
                bottoms out in rear oil seal carrier.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
